This paper proposes an approach to instance-level image segmentation using deep fully convolutional regression networks. The paper focuses on improving semantic category segmentation accuracy, which is critical for achieving good performance in instance-level segmentation. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the PASCAL VOC 2012 dataset, which is commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper discusses the importance of online bootstrapping during training, which is a technique commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) research.
